HEADWORD: Priggism
<hw>Prig"gism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being priggish; the manners of a prig.</def>
<rj><au>Ed. Rev.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Roguery; thievery.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Fielding.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prighte</ent>⟦br⟧
